CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 28, 1945, pg. 5, reads: "West Coast Peaches - Mrs. Alma Davis, cute and blonde, and dark haired Mrs. Dorothy Lee of Los Angeles have 'done' Pittsburgh up brown since their advent a week or so ago. They were the house guests of Mr. and Mrs. Luvernis Lee of Camp Street and were the center of much social attention during their stay. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Alma Davis wearing butterfly patterned dress, and Dorothy Le,e posed in South Park lodge
